.TH CMUX-ORCHESTRATOR 1 "2026-07-21" "HEARTH" "HEARTH cmux integration"
.SH NAME
cmux-orchestrator \- triage cmux panes with on-device HEARTH and notify the ones needing attention
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B uv run python scripts/cmux/orchestrator.py
.RB [ --lines
.IR N ]
.RB [ --dry-run ]
.RB [ --socket
.IR PATH ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs one triage sweep over a running cmux: enumerates terminal surfaces, reads each pane's recent
output, asks a
.B local
HEARTH model to classify the pane's state
.RB ( working ,
.BR waiting ,
.BR done ,
.BR error ),
and fires
.B cmux notify
for the panes that need a human. Lets you run many agents in parallel and be told which one to look at.
.PP
Pane text is sent only to the local HEARTH router
.RB ( build_toolset ,
escalation off); the cmux client speaks only the local Unix socket. There is no other network path,
so the sweep stays loopback-only under
.BR cmux-sealed (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --lines " N"
Screen lines per pane to read (default 80).
.TP
.B --dry-run
Triage and print, but send no notifications.
.TP
.BI --socket " PATH"
cmux socket path (default
.BR $CMUX_SOCKET_PATH ).
.SH PRIORITIES
.IP \(bu 3
.BR waiting ", " error " \(-> attention (notify)."
.IP \(bu 3
.BR done " \(-> info (notify)."
.IP \(bu 3
.BR working ", unknown \(-> quiet (no notify)."
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR cmux-sealed (1),
.B docs/cmux/RUNBOOK_orchestrator.md ,
.B scripts/cmux/orchestrator_demo.py
.SH CAVEAT
Triage quality is bounded by the local model; treat notifications as a routing hint, not ground truth.
